        <div class="container" style="font-size:18px; font-weight:300;margin-top:50px;margin-bottom:50px;">
            <b>Self-portrayal</b>. Currently, as a Ph.D. student, I'm a research assistant at <a href="http://www.wvu.edu/" target="_blank">West Virginia University</a>. Previously I was a visiting student at <a href="http://www.umd.edu/" target="_blank">University of Maryland College Park</a>. My research is mainly about Deep Learning and its applications in Computer Vision and Speech Processing. In particular, I am interested in implementing Convolutional Neural Networks and vision-inspired techniques in Speech Processing and Speaker Recognition. 
            <br><br>
            My deep interest is in Machine Learning, Image Processing, Computer Vision and Deep Learning led to having an in-depth(hopefully!), practical understanding of machine learning techniques, with a specific emphasis on image processing and computer vision. In particular, gaining the practical knowledge of learning techniques including clustering, linear regression, SVM, decision trees, neural networks, LDA, PCA, and deep learning been as a consequence. I'm also experienced in transfer learning, data, and image pre-processing techniques. Moreover, I'm interested in developing software packages and open-source projects. Please refer to my <a href="https://github.com/astorfi/" target="_blank">GitHub page</a> to take a look at my repositories.

